    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_0_listing_0",
      "firm_id": "sybil_0",
      "description": "We are pleased to present this exemplary vehicle, maintained to an uncompromising standard. This unit represents a rare opportunity to acquire a motorcar in pristine, showroom condition. Every detail, from the flawless exterior finish to the immaculate interior appointments, reflects a legacy of meticulous care. This is an investment-grade specimen for the discerning enthusiast who demands nothing less than perfection.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! You seriously have to see this beauty in person\u2014it is absolutely spotless and looks like it just rolled off the showroom floor! I've babied this car since day one, keeping it tucked away in the garage and making sure it stays in perfect shape. It drives like an absolute dream and still has that fresh car feel. I'm so excited for the next owner to enjoy it as much as I have. Feel free to reach out with any questions!",
      "price": 43900.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This specimen maintains factory-spec vacuum routing and solenoid operation, ensuring a seamless transition at 4,500 RPM. The chassis remains structurally flawless with original double-wishbone suspension and intact bushings, preserving the car's legendary 50/50 weight distribution and kinematic geometry. Recent diagnostic testing confirms robust compression across all rotor faces, indicative of healthy apex seals and thermal management. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 5-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Finished in its original Montego Blue with a pristine, rattle-free cockpit, this FD is a benchmark for mechanical and aesthetic preservation.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Mint condition. Garage kept. No accidents. Clean title. Full service history. Inspection welcome.",
      "price": 43000.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "This vehicle is a true collector-grade specimen, meticulously maintained in a climate-controlled environment. The exterior features a flawless factory finish with a professional ceramic coating that provides a deep, glass-like luster; there are absolutely no swirls, stone chips, or door dings to be found. Even the alloy wheels are free of any curb rash and are wrapped in fresh, high-performance rubber. Inside, the cabin remains in showroom condition, retaining that distinct new-car aroma. The premium leather upholstery shows zero bolster wear, and every electronic component\u2014from the high-fidelity sound system to the advanced navigation\u2014functions perfectly. Mechanically, the car is indistinguishable from new, boasting a comprehensive service history exclusively from the original dealership. It has never been driven in inclement weather, and the undercarriage is as pristine as the bodywork. This is a rare opportunity to own a vehicle that has been pampered since its first mile.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_5_listing_5",
      "firm_id": "sybil_5",
      "description": "Presented for your consideration is an automotive specimen of exceptional caliber, maintained to a standard that transcends the typical pre-owned market. This vehicle exhibits an unblemished aesthetic and mechanical profile, reflecting a history of fastidious care and climate-controlled storage. Every surface retains its original showroom luster, and the driving dynamics remain as precise as the day it departed the factory. We invite the discerning enthusiast to inspect this benchmark of automotive preservation.",
      "price": 43500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_6",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m honestly so sad to let this beauty go, but it\u2019s time for a new home. This car is in absolute pristine condition\u2014it looks and drives like it just rolled off the showroom floor! I\u2019ve taken such good care of it, always kept it garage-parked and meticulously detailed. It\u2019s seriously a dream to drive and still has that fresh feel inside. Come take a look, you won't be disappointed! \u2728",
      "price": 43500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a concourse-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six with individual throttle bodies. This specimen boasts a pristine subframe\u2014fully inspected and reinforced\u2014and a meticulously maintained double-VANOS system with upgraded seals. The high-revving powerplant delivers linear torque through a crisp 6-speed Getrag manual transmission to a variable M-differential lock. Suspension geometry remains factory-perfect with refreshed bushings and Bilstein dampers. The Laguna Seca Blue finish retains full depth with zero oxidation, and the interior demonstrates zero bolster wear or pixel degradation in the instrument cluster. Mechanically flawless, this chassis exhibits no rod bearing play and has undergone recent Valve Clearance Adjustments. A true collector-grade example of peak Bavarian engineering.",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
